the recently observed oxygen\nemission data by the Hubble Space Telescope. We find that while the simulations\nare globally consistent with brighter oxygen emission at dusk than at dawn, the\norbital evolution of the asymmetries in our simulations can be improved by\nameliorating the O$_2$ source & loss rates, and possibly adsorption onto the\nregolith.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 27 Apr 2018 16:32:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-27"}
